obo:UBERON_0002421  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_3688  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig 3 Neuronal activity potentiates GLKAP-DLG2 interaction\nLiteral: \"We next analyzed the effect of neuronal activity on GKAP-DLC2 interaction. To enhance neuronal activity, we used a specific blocker of transient outward voltage-dependent potassium currents, 4-AP (1 mM. BRET signal between RLuc8- GKAP and Venus-DLC2 in hippocampal neurons was recorded\nbefore and during 4-AP exposure (Fig. 3A).\"After 4-AP exposure, the mean BRET signal increased in soma and dendrites\"\nFig 6 GKAP-DLC2 interaction enhances NMDA synaptic currents\nLiteral \"Because GKAP-DLC2 interaction promotes synaptic localizationb of\nPSD-95, we investigated the modulatory role of this protein assembly on endogenous NMDA current. Neurons transfected with CFP-GKAP or CFP-GKAPmut were recorded in the whole-cell configuration using the patch-clamp technique and transiently perfused with NMDA. GKAP induced a increase in NMDA currents. \" We further studied the modulatory action of the GKAP-DLC2\ninteraction on NMDA current at the synaptic level by analyzing the slow component of miniature excitatory postsynaptic currents (mEPSCs) carried by NMDA currents. The NMDA component was measured 7 mseconds after the peak\namplitude of averaged mEPSCs, in untransfected neurons or neurons transfected with GKAP or GKAPmut. Overexpression of GKAP significantly (P,0.05) increased the amplitude of the synaptic NMDA component.\". Experimental description: Mouse hippocampal cultures\nLiteral \"Hippocampal neuronal primary cultures were prepared from embryonic day 17.5 mice and grown in neurobasal medium\"\n\n21/11/2017 Pim\n- Overexpressed DLGAP1 protein is from rat species. Personal communication with the author:\n\"the GKAP1a cDNA was from rat.\"\n- Annotation to the rat species was made." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3688" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

